I come to this spot every day, while the food is amazing the service really needs to keep up. the cashier is very friendly as long as its not busy, and when I say busy I mean literally one more customer besides yourself, the moment more than one customer comes the dude behind the counter is visibly stressed you can't even ask how long the food will take because they will keep saying only one minute (even though you're there for 20 mins already). they either need to get competent staff or at least increase the number since the guys at the moment clearly can't handle the rush they get. another thing is that regardless of how busy it is the cashier's mood shouldn't change and should remain professional. this is not the case however as the guy behind counter gets very rude when there's a bunch of orders. overall amazing fresh food but very off putting customer service

Walked by as a cop was walking out with his to go order. I asked how the food was there and he said "excellent, you have to try it". So we did and we're VERY happy with what they have! The host/owner was very personable and we trusted everything he suggested. It was my introduction to Pakistani food so I really didn't know what to expect. Owner dropped off a yogurt/salad dish that we didn't order and just told us to it, which we did and it was DELICIOUS!! The lamb dish & beef kabob were very well spiced and portioned. We also had masala fries that I want the recipe for! Can't wait to go back!!
